Animals do have the sweat glands that cause BO though. Humans have two types, eccrine on most of our bodies which more or less just secrete water and a tiny bit of salt and apocrine in our armpits/groin that also secrete proteins and lipids. BO happens when bacteria decompose these, they don't have a smell to them otherwise. In some animals like horses and marsupials they have apocrine glands all over their body and its actually their primary way of regulating their body temp.
